{"_id":"76brnhZp36bxcZaJ","name":"Twist","type":"Monster","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":15,"max":15}},"biography":{"description":"<p>The Warp Consortium tries to hide it, but it is an open secret that travelling the warp is not entirely safe. A very small fraction of people who do so are changed by the experience, mutated from their original DNA, and become what are known as twists. It seems that those who face the warp directly by leaving a vessel in warp space are most likely to mutate, but some denizens just seem more susceptible. Warp touched are even more likely to become twisted, failing to control the glyphs they use. Twists are mutated versions of their original species, and they are invariably driven insane by the experience. They are often shunned and feared, for although DNA manipulation is relatively widespread, mutations caused by the warp seem resistant to cure, and if anything can become more severe if tampered with. As a result twists often live on the fringes of society, as pirates and raiders, and draw the ire of the Hegemony. To generate a twist, roll on the lesser and greater mutations table beginning on page 154.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":5,"adventuringSkills":5},"token":{"name":"Twist","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[{"_id":"Zi6KluNsi9vGubBp","name":"Mutations","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>To generate a twist, roll on the&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\"><a class=\"entity-link content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"warlock.rollable-tables-warpstar\" data-id=\"AOG6LVsoaumRP9PT\"> Lesser Mutations</a> </span><span style=\"font-family: var(--font-primary); font-size: var(--font-size-14);\">and <a class=\"entity-link content-link\" draggable=\"true\" data-pack=\"warlock.rollable-tables-warpstar\" data-id=\"4HmUOZBldJVpU3di\"> Greater Mutations</a>&nbsp;tables.</span></p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.76brnhZp36bxcZaJ"}}}
{"_id":"7YZYqEitfqt3aejE","name":"Vornin","type":"Monster","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":2,"max":2},"stamina":{"value":18,"max":18}},"biography":{"description":"<p>Savage killers who make excellent mercenaries and bounty hunters, the Vornin are known and feared across the Chorus. Their homeworld, Excet Prime, was destroyed by a warp storm brought about through Warp Consortium experiments, and they have harboured a hatred of the Consortium and by extension the rest of the authority figures of the Chorus ever since. Tall, whip-strong and agile, the Vornin make excellent servants if destruction and death are your aims.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":9,"adventuringSkills":0},"token":{"name":"Vornin","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[{"_id":"xd4Ww76ynxD3dBxg","name":"Tracking","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The denizen is excellent at tracking others by scent or using another sense. Treat its adventuring skill at three times the normal level for tests involving tracking.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.abilities-warpstar.BxYF2EeqOjtsAxja"}}},{"_id":"Z0oomvYVGzogQ52i","name":"Hide","type":"Armour","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":""},"reductionRoll":"1d6"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.7YZYqEitfqt3aejE"}}}
{"_id":"9TNsZzukmKRUrDp6","name":"Anthromorph","type":"Monster","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/werewolf.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":10,"max":10}},"biography":{"description":"<p>When the Warp Consortium created a genetic arc to ensure humanity's survival in the event of the Xendri events, they mined old Earth for DNA. Some of the more ambitious scientists in the Consortium team decided to create a number of hybrid creatures at the same time, so that Earth's animals could live on. Eventually, the interest in the designs waned and they were sold to the Hegemony and weaponised. Anthromorphs are animal/ human hybrids created for various missions. Brutes, typically created from elephants, rhinos, bulls or bears, are deployed for pure aggression. Stalkers are stealth specialists and assassins and created from such animals as cats, rats, and tigers. Tinkerers are highly intelligent tool users and tech specialists and created from apes, raccoons, beavers etc. The genetic splicing of Human and animal DNA tends to create more extreme personalities and Anthromorphs are often somewhat larger than life figures.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":6,"adventuringSkills":0},"token":{"name":"Anthromorph","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/werewolf.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.9TNsZzukmKRUrDp6"}}}
{"_id":"AcSzcK8245bIKybO","name":"Human, Spacer","type":"Monster","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":9,"max":9}},"biography":{"description":"<p>Born in zero gravity (not just on a spacecraft, most of which have artificial gravity), spacers are adept at managing without gravity, and don't loose muscle mass etc. as normal humans do in such an environment. They are however very slender and less robust than even light worlders.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":5,"adventuringSkills":5},"token":{"name":"Human, Spacer","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[{"_id":"oV5ZTXaAAHphQvP0","name":"Brittle","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This denizen is susceptible to impact damage. If smashing weapons or guns attack them successfully, the damage is rolled twice and the higher value is applied.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.abilities-warpstar.Q6EuVTrS5AmNMRgP"}}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.AcSzcK8245bIKybO"}}}
{"_id":"G42mxFV3rpPNNvCf","name":"Amoeba","type":"Monster","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/slime.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":20,"max":20}},"biography":{"description":"<p>Blue-black 'puddles' of sentient organic matter, the predatory amoebis thrive on the strong emotions felt by intelligent beings. They seek to dissolve their prey, being satiated by the fear and death throes of their victims. Any damage causes amoebis to divide in half, splitting the starting stamina between the creatures, both retaining the power to dissolve.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":6,"adventuringSkills":0},"token":{"name":"Amoeba","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/slime.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[{"_id":"0Kxoh1jvJKyiuRdV","name":"Formless","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The body of this denizen has no real form, so it may slide under doors, squeeze through narrow spaces etc. as if it were a thick, viscous liquid.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.abilities-warpstar.lRPBCjyFjVAPS8NP"}}},{"_id":"MGuDNnZ0tMYOq7pc","name":"Dissolve","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This being is able to dissolve matter, or exudes an acidic venom. All successful attacks cause it to splash out the venom, and any time it is successfully struck in melee the attacker must test their luck. On a fail, their weapon is destroyed.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":-100000,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.abilities-warpstar.RO81Vt0zhim8dOIV"}}},{"_id":"kQVEiOI0exkSf6Fs","name":"Amoeba","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>On zero&nbsp;stamina, splits into two&nbsp;amoeba with 10 stamina&nbsp;each.&nbsp;</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":-200000,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}},{"_id":"Nyg92KJyGX1dCEjx","name":"Acid","type":"Weapon","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":"—"},"damage":{"roll":"1d6+2","type":{"value":"Energy"}},"skill":{"value":"Weapon Skill"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.G42mxFV3rpPNNvCf"}}}
{"_id":"Iux8fplUiyFEvBKL","name":"Nova Guard","type":"Monster","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/robot-helmet.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":3,"max":3},"stamina":{"value":22,"max":22}},"biography":{"description":"<p>Wearing powered-armour and sporting powerful pulse weaponry, the Nova Guard are feared as a military organisation while also being revered as the last defence of the Chorus. Their troopers are seen over most Chorus worlds, space ports and orbital structures, and their cruisers and needleships are a common sight on the space lanes. The Nova Guard also act as customs and trade enforcement for the Merchant Combine, and back up the Warp Consortium on their missions to find warp touched. The Autarch also employs the famous 'Purple guard' as their own military force, rumoured to be the best soldiers in the Chorus.&nbsp;</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":10,"adventuringSkills":0},"token":{"name":"Nova Guard","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/robot-helmet.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[{"_id":"i53In80Julwekwlm","name":"Flying (antigrav pack)","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>Using wings, engines or similar, this denizen can fly. Treat this as normal movement, but ignoring barriers that can be flown over at the game master's discretion. This being cannot be engaged in melee combat whilst flying unless it chooses to attack, in which case it can be targeted.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.abilities-warpstar.Gljx55OGyM7ZmvqY"}}},{"_id":"KIyuFSYOnalZIaw2","name":"Powered armour","type":"Armour","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":""},"reductionRoll":"2d6"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.Iux8fplUiyFEvBKL"}}}
{"_id":"LUewJCMaOoyssLT3","name":"Warp Tick","type":"Monster","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/insect-jaws.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":8,"max":8}},"biography":{"description":"<p>The large insect-like creatures hover at the broken edges of warp space, where they attach themselves to passing spacecraft. They are dangerous pests, chewing into hull structure and cabling, and if left unhindered can easily reduce a spacecraft to debris in a few days. Sadly, the only way to remove them is to exit the craft and blast them off, and they can be very nasty!</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":4,"adventuringSkills":0},"token":{"name":"Warp Tick","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/insect-jaws.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[{"_id":"3hoT1UF4TlAQSvjC","name":"Shell","type":"Armour","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":""},"reductionRoll":"1d3"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}},{"_id":"sut7Yy8KTYoc4r6B","name":"Claw","type":"Weapon","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":"—"},"damage":{"roll":"1d6","type":{"value":"Slashing"}},"skill":{"value":"Weapon Skill"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}},{"_id":"kuvvBYrN827BGKgv","name":"Fang","type":"Weapon","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":"—"},"damage":{"roll":"1d6","type":{"value":"Piercing"}},"skill":{"value":"Weapon Skill"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.LUewJCMaOoyssLT3"}}}
{"_id":"M3dD36UTMV5pmFhW","name":"Fruiting Dead","type":"Monster","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/shambling-zombie.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":15,"max":15}},"biography":{"description":"<p>Shambling undead humanoids infested with a warpspawned fungal mass that seeks to pacify living beings with the soporific spores they exude so they can leech them of nutrients. If the fruiting dead are struck in combat, those at close range must test their luck or sleep until medically revived. Leeching takes [[/roll 1d6+1]] rounds and the victim is left as a desiccated husk that will prey on other beings.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":7,"adventuringSkills":4},"token":{"name":"Fruiting Dead","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/shambling-zombie.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[{"_id":"ZvtfdjDawR0lpbHN","name":"Soporific spores","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>If the fruiting dead are struck in combat, those at close range must test their luck or sleep until medically revived. Leeching takes [[/roll 1d6+1]] rounds and the victim is left as a desiccated husk that will prey on other beings.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}},{"_id":"tEKNPyPABHLZWeS4","name":"Claws","type":"Weapon","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":"—"},"damage":{"roll":"2d6","type":{"value":"Slashing"}},"skill":{"value":"Weapon Skill"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.M3dD36UTMV5pmFhW"}}}
{"_id":"W1Kijw51faI2ADwL","name":"Human","type":"Monster","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":15,"max":15}},"biography":{"description":"<p>A standard human, as would have be indistinguishable from the multitudes on Earth before that world was destroyed. This set of statistics can be used for the majority of humans in the Chorus, even though such individuals may be unique in appearance. Grosser changes to the human form (extra limbs, a tail, wings etc.) can be represented by denizen abilities as appropriate.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":5,"adventuringSkills":5},"token":{"name":"Human","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.W1Kijw51faI2ADwL"}}}
{"_id":"WcNGBxbzny54cNmU","name":"Jondo","type":"Monster","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/gorilla.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":26,"max":26}},"biography":{"description":"<p>The Jondo are large, ape-like beings whose home world is lost to the distant past. Intelligent, they are large and strong, but tend to have placid natures and are prone to self-analysis and philosophising. They are often found around space ports and on orbitals, where their strength is valued. They also show a remarkable aptitude for zero gravity, which makes they useful as mechanics and engineers.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":9,"adventuringSkills":0},"token":{"name":"Jondo","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/gorilla.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.WcNGBxbzny54cNmU"}}}
{"_id":"bBgkzKrnaKKA2C5o","name":"Kronux","type":"Monster","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/orc-head.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":18,"max":18}},"biography":{"description":"<p>A species that was initially contacted on Gald-Aru VIII, the kronux have become a menace across parts of the Chorus. Seemingly intelligent but violent and utterly devoid of recognisable emotions, the kronux seem to be intent on spreading themselves across a large volume of space. They do this by converting genetic matter into new kronux - the genetic matter in question being that of other intelligent beings. This creates all manner of hybrid beings that share physical traits with the kronux and with the host species, but no matter how 'kronux' a being may be, once it is infected with the kronux DNA, it becomes as unthinkingly destructive as the original species. Infection seems to be through some viral agent that converts non-kronux DNA, creating a hybrid that changes slowly over time to become completely kronux. The intelligence of the species can be seen in the secretive and planned way in which they infect new host planetary systems. The Hegemony is sworn to stamp out the kronux menace.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":8,"adventuringSkills":0},"token":{"name":"Kronux","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/orc-head.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[{"_id":"jDV0O0H58ePBkcNM","name":"Dissolve","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This being is able to dissolve matter, or exudes an acidic venom. All successful attacks cause it to splash out the venom, and any time it is successfully struck in melee the attacker must test their luck. On a fail, their weapon is destroyed.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.abilities-warpstar.RO81Vt0zhim8dOIV"}}},{"_id":"BsVVlENUTfAn13Df","name":"Regenerating","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>The being is able to recover damage. Every round the being regains [[/roll 1d6]] stamina, up to a maximum of its starting value.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.abilities-warpstar.qrwCqsvK7MVZpwtm"}}},{"_id":"3COAyu1mVOoPIdtX","name":"Claw","type":"Weapon","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":"—"},"damage":{"roll":"2d6+4","type":{"value":"Slashing"}},"skill":{"value":"Weapon Skill"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}},{"_id":"8Qxt3qRkuePxxADH","name":"Fang","type":"Weapon","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":"—"},"damage":{"roll":"2d6+4","type":{"value":"Piercing"}},"skill":{"value":"Weapon Skill"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}},{"_id":"jWzVmQTGqMTYbu4A","name":"Tough skin","type":"Armour","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":""},"reductionRoll":"1d6"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.bBgkzKrnaKKA2C5o"}}}
{"_id":"cGLpxaVUUZfVERpp","name":"Human, Light Worlder","type":"Monster","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":13,"max":13}},"biography":{"description":"<p>Born on worlds with low gravity, light worlders as they are known, tend to be tall and slender, lacking muscle mass but having increased dexterity and nimbleness.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":6,"adventuringSkills":5},"token":{"name":"Human, Light Worlder","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.cGLpxaVUUZfVERpp"}}}
{"_id":"hMxVzt0qwfDs6RMx","name":"Nodes","type":"Monster","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/cyborg-face.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":2,"max":2},"stamina":{"value":21,"max":21}},"biography":{"description":"<p>Living cybernetic implants that infect people and turn them into drone soldiers of a collective intellect, nodes are highly dangerous machine organisms that have spread from a location outside of the Chorus. Individuals infected by nodes show cybernetic growths on their bodies, particularly on the regions holding their brains, and attack with a single minded purpose. Their aim is always the same - to subdue individuals and infect them with more nodes, which they create from captured matter. The Nova Guard have been fighting the nodes for many years, and it is not easy to say which side is winning.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":9,"adventuringSkills":0},"token":{"name":"Nodes","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/robot-helmet.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[{"_id":"ToLiKwiDYK5RBtMj","name":"Toughened Skin","type":"Armour","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":""},"reductionRoll":"1d3"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.hMxVzt0qwfDs6RMx"}}}
{"_id":"ox5UW1zKjW3cRFA4","name":"Warp Entity","type":"Monster","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/spectre.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":15,"max":15}},"biography":{"description":"<p>Sometimes things from the warp manifest in the real. These creatures are called warp entities, and they can be extremely dangerous. Often, such manifestations begin as a spectral warp beast, a ghostly form that is visible and audible, but unable to interact with the real world. However, should such a fragment accumulate enough psychic energy such as fear or anger, it can use that power to manifest in the real. Typically, these events happen when travelling through warp space. It starts by the appearance of the warp ghost, spreading fear and terror through telekinesis, but feeds on that fear to eventually burst forth in a monstrous physical manifestation. Typically, this entity thus created appears as a pale, thin humanoid, but with strange and distinctive features and powers that seem to manifest randomly.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":5,"adventuringSkills":0},"token":{"name":"Warp entity","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/spectre.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[{"_id":"TB6EOPWw629SVCrO","name":"Warp denizen","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This creature does not exist in the material plane. It can only be harmed by warp-based attacks such as glyphs, and can pass through solid barriers such as doors and walls with ease.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.abilities-warpstar.egcXNZtBqaWvPlHn"}}},{"_id":"xIjuWw46uVJkhnDH","name":"Ethereal claws","type":"Weapon","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":"—"},"damage":{"roll":"2d6","type":{"value":"Slashing"}},"skill":{"value":"Weapon Skill"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.ox5UW1zKjW3cRFA4"}}}
{"_id":"sJr1qGE2pEgLyqAA","name":"Human, Heavy Worlder","type":"Monster","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":17,"max":17}},"biography":{"description":"<p>Beings that hail from worlds with very strong gravities are called heavy worlders. Compared to normal members of their species, they tend to be squad and muscular, with greater strength but at a cost in grace and suppleness.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":6,"adventuringSkills":5},"token":{"name":"Human, Heavy Worlder","img":"icons/svg/mystery-man.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.sJr1qGE2pEgLyqAA"}}}
{"_id":"to38XaC0kWdUdAW8","name":"Borr","type":"Monster","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/boar.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":2,"max":2},"stamina":{"value":32,"max":32}},"biography":{"description":"<p>These fearsome-looking horned quadrupeds are surprisingly cultured and urbane. They appear as animals, wearing no technology or clothing, but they can speak and employ robots to help them when required. They consider their bestial appearance a mark of pride, a connection to the past and their own culture. Often in the Chorus they take roles which either suit their fearsome appearance, such as acting as enforcers or hunters, of conversely those that lead off from their intelligence and culture, such as acting as translators, diplomats and composers.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":8,"adventuringSkills":0},"token":{"name":"Borr","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/boar.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[{"_id":"1EAdmklvB7H7aKu3","name":"Claw","type":"Weapon","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":"—"},"damage":{"roll":"2d6+1","type":{"value":"Slashing"}},"skill":{"value":"Weapon Skill"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}},{"_id":"xRp5hY7vqPuYFSB7","name":"Fang","type":"Weapon","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":"—"},"damage":{"roll":"2d6+1","type":{"value":"Piercing"}},"skill":{"value":"Weapon Skill"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}},{"_id":"tsZr7V8tCBBGjAR1","name":"Hide","type":"Armour","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":""},"reductionRoll":"1d6"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.to38XaC0kWdUdAW8"}}}
{"_id":"xHBUmij6RjXs2GTT","name":"Warp Dragon","type":"Monster","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/spiked-dragon-head.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":4,"max":4},"stamina":{"value":67,"max":67}},"biography":{"description":"<p>As Warp-born creatures, Warp Dragons begin life as egg-shaped Warp crystals, and can eventually grow to immense size in the wilds of Warp space. As Warp Dragons grow, so do their highly prized crystalline 'wings', actually powerful capacitors for Warp Energy which enables these beasts to project powerful warp blasts and move through space and air. The largest of their kind are able to emit warp blasts capable of splitting Hegemony battle-cruisers in half. Hunted across the galaxy, there is also a lucrative trade in harvesting Warp Dragon eggs, for young Warp Dragons have become fashionable pets amongst the nobles of the Chorus.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":16,"adventuringSkills":0},"token":{"name":"Warp Dragon","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/spiked-dragon-head.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[{"_id":"BYkn4lBdN7iJjqph","name":"Warp denizen","type":"Ability","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>This creature does not exist in the material plane. It can only be harmed by warp-based attacks such as glyphs, and can pass through solid barriers such as doors and walls with ease.</p>"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.world.abilities-warpstar.egcXNZtBqaWvPlHn"}}},{"_id":"n7890fAtM4lo6xMk","name":"Energy blast","type":"Weapon","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":"—"},"damage":{"roll":"4d6","type":{"value":"Energy"}},"skill":{"value":"Weapon Skill"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}},{"_id":"aP80qEKjQibsHm6v","name":"Crystalline hide","type":"Armour","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":""},"reductionRoll":"2d6"},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.xHBUmij6RjXs2GTT"}}}
{"_id":"yN6M15JJGsHZQPK0","name":"Skritter","type":"Monster","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/rat.svg","data":{"resources":{"actionsPerRound":{"value":1,"max":1},"stamina":{"value":8,"max":8}},"biography":{"description":"<p>Originating from the dense jungles of Arzuli, these one-metre long scaly vermin have long reptilian tails, sharp claws and teeth strong enough to bite through metal. Skritters are a nuisance across the Chorus of a Million Worlds. Skritters make nests in piles of scrap metal and cabling. Their urine is acidic; you can tell if you have a skritter problem from the burns marking the holds of infested ships. Skritters are a common cause for malfunctions as they eat their way through crucial hardware.</p>"},"type":"","weaponSkill":5,"adventuringSkills":0},"token":{"name":"Skritters","img":"systems/warlock/assets/icons/monsters/rat.svg","displayName":0,"actorLink":false,"width":1,"height":1,"scale":1,"mirrorX":false,"mirrorY":false,"lockRotation":false,"rotation":0,"alpha":1,"vision":false,"dimSight":0,"brightSight":0,"sightAngle":0,"light":{"alpha":0.5,"angle":0,"bright":0,"coloration":1,"dim":0,"gradual":true,"luminosity":0.5,"saturation":0,"contrast":0,"shadows":0,"animation":{"speed":5,"intensity":5,"reverse":false},"darkness":{"min":0,"max":1}},"disposition":-1,"displayBars":0,"bar1":{"attribute":null},"bar2":{"attribute":null},"flags":{},"randomImg":false},"items":[{"_id":"MS7JlhI76wjOqE2o","name":"Claw","type":"Weapon","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":"—"},"damage":{"roll":"1d6+4","type":{"value":"Slashing"}},"skill":{"value":"Weapon Skill"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}},{"_id":"XYDAa5TKR5DBB8iU","name":"Fang","type":"Weapon","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"","isEquipped":true,"type":{"value":"—"},"damage":{"roll":"1d6+4","type":{"value":"Piercing"}},"skill":{"value":"Weapon Skill"}},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{}}],"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"XMfgoFiiE1BZBDoZ":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.warlock.bestiary-warpstar.yN6M15JJGsHZQPK0"}}}
